## How polymarket.tips Approaches Tracking

The tracker at polymarket.tips focuses specifically on surfacing convergence signals from verified top performers. Rather than showing you a firehose of every trade from every wallet, it curates the signal that matters most. The system continuously monitors the positions of the top 50 traders by verified PnL, flags when multiple traders independently enter the same side of a market, and presents this information in a clean interface that requires no blockchain expertise to interpret. The emphasis on verified PnL matters enormously. Anyone can make a few lucky trades or manipulate a short-term record. The traders surfaced by polymarket.tips have demonstrated edge over meaningful sample sizes, which is the only reliable indicator of genuine skill versus survivorship bias. When these traders converge, the tracker surfaces it within minutes.

## Practical Applications for Different Trading Styles

A Polymarket tracker serves different purposes depending on how you engage with prediction markets. For active traders, convergence signals provide entry timing and conviction sizing. If you already believed the Iran peace deal market was mispriced but were uncertain about timing, seeing three top traders independently add to YES positions might accelerate your decision. For passive observers who check markets weekly rather than daily, a tracker serves as a filter. Instead of manually scanning dozens of markets, you can focus your limited attention on the handful where smart money is actively positioning. This is particularly valuable during periods of high volatility, like the current geopolitical uncertainty, when markets move quickly and catching the right side early matters more than usual. Even for pure researchers interested in prediction market accuracy, tracker data provides a layer of analysis beyond raw prices, showing not just what the crowd believes but what the most informed subset of the crowd believes.

## The Edge That Compounds Over Time

Following smart money is not about finding a single winning trade. It is about systematically improving your base rate across dozens or hundreds of decisions. A Polymarket tracker that surfaces genuine convergence signals gives you a structural advantage that compounds. Over time, you develop intuition for which types of markets see the strongest smart money activity, which traders have edge in which domains, and how quickly convergence signals tend to resolve. The current environment, with massive volume flowing through [Polymarket](https://polymarket.com/?r=POLYTips) on Fed decisions, Middle East developments, and upcoming elections, offers unusually rich data for anyone willing to pay attention to what top traders are actually doing. The information is public. The question is whether you have the tools to see it clearly.

